 ployers with insured health plans might receive rebates if their issuers d
 id not meet their medical loss ratio (MLR) percentage for 2024.\nTip: Any 
 rebate amount that qualifies as a plan asset under ERISA must be used for 
 the exclusive benefit of the plan's participants and beneficiaries. Plan s
 ponsors should use the plan asset portion of the rebate within three month
 s of receiving it to avoid ERISA's trust requirements.\n\n
