 ctors with 50+)\n\nWhat: The EEO-1 Report (Employer Information Report) is
  a mandatory annual filing for large private employers (100+ employees) an
 d certain federal contractors (50+ employees) to submit workforce demograp
 hic data on job category\, sex\, race\, and ethnicity to the EEOC<https://
 www.eeoc.gov/data/eeo-1-employer-information-report-statistics>\, helping 
 the agency monitor employment practices and identify discrimination patter
 ns. Data is collected for a "snapshot" pay period in the last quarter of t
 he year (Oct-Dec)\, with specific filing deadlines set annually by the EEO
 C<https://www.eeoc.gov/newsroom/message-eeoc-acting-chair-lucas-about-open
 ing-2024-eeo-1-component-1-data-collection>.  It is filed through EEOC EEO
 -1 Online Filing System.\n\nWhen: Anticipated June 2026\n
