 IHAKAHALIHALgHAMIHAMgHAIAIAA&sclient=gws-wiz-serp> for the next plan year 
 is a mandatory document employers must give employees at least 90 days bef
 ore the new year\, detailing the tax-free reimbursement amount\, plan date
 s\, rules for premium tax credits (PTCs)\, and how to use the benefit\, en
 suring employees understand it's for individual insurance (like on the Mar
 ketplace) and how it affects their PTC eligibility\, preventing tax issues
 . It's crucial for compliance and informs employees about their options fo
 r coverage and potential SEP (Special Enrollment Period) access.\n\nWhen: 
 Provide the required annual notice at least 90 days before the start of th
 e plan year (e.g.\, by Oct. 2\, 2026 for a Jan. 1\, 2027 plan year). (IRS/
 EBSA guidance)\n\n\n
