BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Who: Employers applying for the 28% RDS for plan years beginnin
 g Jan 1\, 2027\n\nWhat: The Medicare Part D Retiree Drug Subsidy (RDS) pro
 gram helps employers and unions lower costs for providing prescription dru
 g coverage to their Medicare-eligible retirees by reimbursing them for a p
 ortion of those drug expenses\, specifically 28% of costs between set annu
 al thresholds and limits\, provided the employer plan offers at least actu
 arially equivalent coverage to standard Medicare Part D.\n\nWhen: Submit R
 DS application<https://www.rds.cms.hhs.gov/regulations-guidance/important-
 application-deadline-information>\, retiree list<https://www.rds.cms.hhs.g
 ov/user-guide/submit-valid-initial-retiree-list-and-monthly-retiree-list>\
 , and attestation<https://www.cms.gov/medicare/regulations-guidance/promot
 ing-interoperability-programs/registration-attestation> <https://www.cms.g
 ov/medicare/regulations-guidance/promoting-interoperability-programs/regis
 tration-attestation> to CMS ~90 days before plan year start (approx. Oct 2
  for Jan 1 plan years).\n
UID:040000008200E00074C5B7101A82E008000000003CEDA3764A8BDC01000000000000000
 0100000003B1722B2DF2C514A98A620A0CF86060E
