BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Who: ALEs and non-ALE self-insured plans using the website-noti
 ce method\n\nWhen: Starting with reporting for the 2024 calendar year (due
  in early 2025)\, and continuing for 2025 (due in 2026)\, the IRS has fina
 lized rules allowing employers to provide Affordable Care Act (ACA) Forms 
 1095-B and 1095-C "on request" rather than automatically mailing them to a
 ll employees. This change\, stemming from the Paperwork Burden Reduction A
 ct\, requires employers to post a "Notice of Availability" on their websit
 e.\n\nWhen: Keep 1095-B/1095-C request notice posted on employer website t
 hrough Oct 15\, 2026.\n
