BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Who: Employers with prescription drug coverage for Medicare-eli
 gible individuals\n\nWhat: Employers with prescription drug coverage must 
 send annual Medicare Part D notices<https://www.google.com/search?q=Medica
 re+Part+D+notices&oq=Medicare+Part+D+Creditable%2FNon-Creditable+Coverage+
 Notices+to+Participants&gs_lcrp=EgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOdIBBzE4OWowajSoAgCwAg
 A&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8&ved=2ahUKEwjAk_fxkp6SAxWRDTQIHQg3CLIQgK4QegQIAR
 AB> by October 15th to all Medicare-eligible individuals (employees\, reti
 rees\, dependents) informing them if their plan is "creditable" (as good a
 s or better than Medicare's) or "non-creditable\," helping them decide on 
 initial Part D enrollment to avoid penalties\; notices can be mailed or el
 ectronically delivered\, but must be prominent\, and plan sponsors also re
 port the coverage status to CMS.\n\nWhen: Provide annual Medicare Part D C
 reditable Coverage Notice<https://www.cms.gov/medicare/employers-plan-spon
 sors/creditable-coverage/model-notice-letters> to participants before the 
 Oct. 15 Part D open enrollment.\n
