BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Who: Employers filing quarterly\n\nWhat: For Q3 2026\, Form 941
  is the Employer's Quarterly Federal Tax Return\, reporting wages and taxe
 s\, with a due date of October 31\, 2026\, for the July-September quarter\
 , filed by most employers\, though smaller ones might use Form 944<https:/
 /www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-944>. Key details include reporting inc
 ome\, social security\, and Medicare taxes\, with e-filing encouraged<http
 s://www.irs.gov/businesses/e-file-employment-tax-forms> and payment rules 
 based on tax liability.\n\nWhen: File Form 941 for Q3 2026 by Oct 31\, 202
 6\; if deposits were timely\, deadline typically extends 10 days. (IRS<htt
 ps://www.irs.gov/instructions/i941>)\n
