BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:Who: Group health plans and issuers subject to CAA gag clause r
 ules\n\nWhat: A Gag Clause Prohibition Compliance Attestation<https://www.
 cms.gov/marketplace/about/oversight/other-insurance-protections/gag-clause
 -prohibition-compliance-attestation> (GCPCA) is an annual self-certificati
 on required by the Consolidated Appropriations Act (CAA)<https://www.cms.g
 ov/marketplace/about/oversight/other-insurance-protections/consolidated-ap
 propriations-act-2021-caa> where health plans and issuers confirm to the g
 overnment (CMS) that their contracts with providers\, TPAs\, and networks 
 do not contain "gag clauses" that restrict sharing provider-specific cost/
 quality data or de-identified claims data. It's an electronic declaration\
 , due annually by December 31\, proving compliance with federal laws (IRC 
 9824\, ERISA 724\, PHS 2799A-9) to protect transparency for patients\, spo
 nsors\, and providers.\n\nWhen: Submit annual gag clause attestation for t
 he plan year by Dec 31\, 2026 (timing may follow agency instructions/porta
 l).\n
